    "body": "Current theory is that it might be to do with processing 512 sync committee messages every slot, at a cost of ~3ms each (on our AWS boxes). That's a whole 1.5 seconds of signature verification!\r\n\r\nUsing single signature verification seems to be marginally slower on our testnet nodes:\r\n\r\n![message_signature_verif](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4452260/125246673-6e67cb80-e335-11eb-8a87-5b03edea4283.png)\r\n\r\n(single verification enabled around 15:30)\r\n\r\nWe may need a batching approach like #2399",
